      "body" : "There is no other benefit except you&#39;re telling the compiler that &quot;I know this is a generic class, but I don&#39;t know or care about the actual type, so instead of giving a concrete type I&#39;m giving the <code>?</code> wildcard.&quot;. If you don&#39;t give the wildcard, the compiler assumes that you either forgot the type or didn&#39;t know the class was generic and will warn you about it."
